Employee Model

The Employee model defines the structure of the form data and includes validation rules.

Example fields:

EmpId

Name
Mail
Phone
Designation
Department
Status
DOJ (Date of Joining)

Validation attributes ensure that required fields are filled and the email/phone formats are correct.

Model Binding

Model Binding automatically maps form input values to a C# model object.

Example:

Form Input
Name = Kaviya
Mail = kaviya@gmail.com

becomes

Employee emp = new Employee();
emp.Name = "Kaviya";
emp.Mail = "kaviya@gmail.com";

This object is then passed to the controller action.

Validation

ASP.NET Core uses Data Annotations to validate the model.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Common validation attributes used:

Required
EmailAddress
Phone
DataType(Date)
Validation is checked in the controller using:

ModelState.IsValid

If validation fails, the form reloads with error messages.
